This paper is about contextualized word representations and their ability to encode sentence structure. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) tasks and uses models such as ELMo and BERT, which are commonly used in NLP research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and model analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper investigates how models encode sentence structure, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses some visualizations to analyze the models, which could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
